<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 8:20PM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Kent,
northern Ionia and southern Montcalm Counties through 945 PM EDT...
At 820 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northeast of Rockford, or 10 miles west of Greenville, moving
east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Greenville...          Stanton...             Belding...
Rockford...            Carson City...         Cedar Springs...
Crystal...             Sidney...              Sheridan...
Sand Lake...           Hubbardston...         Gowen...
Wells Airport...       Palo...                Turk Lake...
Butternut...           Fenwick...             Greenville Municipal...
Kings Corner...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
